The paper deals with a game-theoretic problem of selecting a subset of agents in a directed graph, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory). The problem involves selecting a subset of agents based on their indegrees, which is a graph-theoretic concept, indicating that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions social networks and reputation systems, which are typical topics in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The problem involves designing mechanisms that are strategyproof, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Overall, these five sub-categories seem most relevant to the paper's content.
